WEBVTT

00:22.456 --> 00:26.558
             [¶¶]               

00:43.044 --> 00:46.145
[adults and children chattering]

00:57.324 --> 01:00.325
           [Robert]             
   <i> I hated summer vacation.</i>    

01:02.196 --> 01:06.198
           <i> For me,</i>             
  <i> it wasn't about anticipation,</i>

01:06.200 --> 01:07.800
  <i> it was about preparation.</i>    

01:09.136 --> 01:11.637
        [watch ticking]         

01:26.187 --> 01:29.521
 <i> While everyone else prepared</i>  
         <i> to bare all,</i>          

01:29.523 --> 01:31.757
<i>I had to look for ways to hide.</i> 

01:38.466 --> 01:39.798
There you go, Champ.            

01:39.800 --> 01:41.633
           [Robert]             
   <i> My dad told us he lived</i>     

01:41.635 --> 01:44.336
<i>the full year for our vacation</i>  
       <i> at Rumson Lake.</i>         

01:44.338 --> 01:45.871
        [engine starts]         

01:47.274 --> 01:50.242
           <i> A summer</i>            
  <i> of "rest and relaxation."</i>    

01:51.479 --> 01:53.645
  [Lenore whoops and laughs]    

01:53.647 --> 01:57.816
        [Edgar Winter's         
      "Freeride" playing]       

02:05.292 --> 02:07.259
      -[Lenore laughing]        
  -[indistinct conversation]    

02:07.261 --> 02:08.759
   <i> ¶ The mountain is high ¶</i>    

02:08.762 --> 02:10.895
    <i> ¶ The valley is low ¶</i>      

02:10.898 --> 02:14.700
    <i> ¶ And you're confused</i>      
     <i> On which way to go ¶</i>      

02:14.702 --> 02:18.804
     <i> ¶ So I've come here</i>       
     <i> To give you a hand ¶</i>      

02:18.806 --> 02:23.742
        <i> ¶ And lead you</i>         
   <i> Into the promised land ¶</i>    

02:23.744 --> 02:27.246
      <i> ¶ Come on and take</i>       
   <i> A free ride free ride ¶</i>     

02:27.248 --> 02:31.250
   -[Lenore] Don't do that.     
        -It's my turn.          

02:31.252 --> 02:34.186
          <i> ¶ Come on</i>            
   <i> Let's take a free ride ¶</i>    

02:34.188 --> 02:35.821
          [laughter]            

02:35.823 --> 02:37.623
 [Bobby] Do we have any snacks  
          in the car?           

02:37.625 --> 02:39.291
          -[all] No!            
-[Marty] You want to be adults, 

02:39.293 --> 02:41.193
     then act like adults,      
      but you act like...       

02:41.195 --> 02:42.794
            [Michelle]          
     I'm acting like an adult.  

02:42.796 --> 02:45.164
  Firstly, you don't even act   
        like teenagers.         

02:45.166 --> 02:47.799
         -Excuse me--           
     -Oh, my God, shut up!      

02:47.801 --> 02:50.702
           [Robert]             
 <i> Like I said: I hated summer.</i>  

02:52.373 --> 02:53.939
   <i> ¶ All over the country ¶</i>    

02:53.941 --> 02:56.241
  <i> ¶ I've seen it the same ¶</i>    

02:56.243 --> 03:00.279
      <i> ¶ Nobody's winning</i>       
    <i> At this kind of game ¶</i>     

03:00.281 --> 03:01.947
            [Marty]             
   Everybody grab something.    

03:01.949 --> 03:05.918
   [Michelle] Oh, my gosh--     
      that took forever!        

03:12.459 --> 03:15.294
  [Bobby] Oh man, they should   
     put wheels on these.       

03:16.463 --> 03:17.829
       [loudly exhales]         

03:17.831 --> 03:20.933
   [chattering in distance]     

03:29.543 --> 03:32.344
Bobby Marks to Joanie Williams. 

03:32.346 --> 03:34.413
   Come in, Joanie Williams.    

03:37.718 --> 03:39.418
      Joanie, you there?        

03:46.961 --> 03:48.694
                      Damn it.  

03:58.272 --> 04:00.739
   [Joanie on walkie-talkie]    
         <i> Bobby Marks?</i>          

04:02.776 --> 04:04.443
         You're there.          

04:06.247 --> 04:07.779
        [Joanie laughs]         
<i>We had dinner at the Campbells.</i> 

04:07.781 --> 04:09.681
       <i> It was so dull.</i>         

04:09.683 --> 04:12.384
        [snobby accent]         
     And this is the spoon      
         Napoleon used          

04:12.386 --> 04:14.486
  to feed caviar to his cat.    

04:14.488 --> 04:16.421
        [Joanie laughs]         
           <i> Exactly.</i>            

04:16.423 --> 04:19.458
 <i> I wanted to grab her poetry</i>   
  <i> and throw it on the fire.</i>    

04:19.459 --> 04:20.959
   Oh, God, not the poetry.     

04:20.961 --> 04:23.395
           <i> -Yeah.</i>              
     <i> -Well, don't worry.</i>       

04:23.397 --> 04:25.497
         Your summer's          
  about to get a lot better.    

04:25.499 --> 04:26.732
            <i> Cool.</i>              

04:26.734 --> 04:28.900
   <i> See you tomorrow night.</i>     

04:30.804 --> 04:33.305
      [Marty in distance]       
       In this scenario,        
      you're the mother.        

04:33.307 --> 04:35.274
[Lenore] I'll arrange my classes
   around Bobby's schedule.     

04:35.276 --> 04:37.643
     -It's gonna be fine.       
-[Marty] And what if you can't? 

04:37.645 --> 04:40.679
   What if Bobby gets sick?     
Are you just gonna skip class?  

04:40.681 --> 04:42.981
  -What's your plan, Lenore?    
 -[Lenore] If Bobby gets sick,  

04:42.983 --> 04:44.983
       I will stay home         
       and nurse him...         

04:44.985 --> 04:47.052
  [Robert] <i> My parents didn't</i>    
     <i> used to argue much.</i>       

04:47.054 --> 04:49.354
  <i> Until my mom got involved</i>    
  <i> with the Women's Movement</i>    

04:49.356 --> 04:50.856
      <i> and decided to go</i>        
        <i> to law school.</i>         

04:50.858 --> 04:52.524
            [Marty]             
Because they're just visiting.  

04:52.526 --> 04:54.426
Why do we have to--             
Oh, hi, baby.                   

04:54.428 --> 04:56.628
        -Good morning.          
        -Good morning.          

04:56.630 --> 04:58.563
       -Are you hungry?         
          -Oh, yeah.            

04:58.565 --> 05:00.399
      Is that mine?             

05:00.401 --> 05:02.367
         -The shirt--           
    -Oh, I bought him that.     

05:02.369 --> 05:04.002
   Are you sure?                
   It's too big for him.        

05:04.004 --> 05:07.539
       -Yes, I am sure.         
            -Yeah?              

05:07.541 --> 05:09.007
    It just kinda makes him     
    look bigger.                

05:09.009 --> 05:11.810
Well, he'll grow                
into it.                        

05:11.812 --> 05:13.879
     That's what                
     I'm afraid of, right.      

05:13.881 --> 05:15.080
       It's comfortable.        

05:15.082 --> 05:17.082
     I'm sure it is comfortable,

05:17.084 --> 05:18.884
          but you know--        
          it's like a tent.     

05:18.886 --> 05:21.053
     -You look lost in it.      
      -[Lenore] Morning.        

05:21.055 --> 05:23.021
     -Morning, beautiful.       
     -[Lenore] Hi, honey.       

05:23.023 --> 05:24.956
        -How you doing?         
     -[Michelle] I'm good.      

05:24.958 --> 05:28.026
           [Lenore]             
  Happy first day of summer!    

05:28.028 --> 05:29.695
  Do you want some breakfast?   

05:29.697 --> 05:30.962
       I made everything        
        I can think of.         

05:30.964 --> 05:32.597
I'm so excited                  
for this morning.               

05:32.599 --> 05:34.399
                 I have to go   
                 to orientation 

05:34.401 --> 05:35.967
       and they'll probably have
       food there or something. 

05:35.969 --> 05:37.669
       -[Lenore] Really?        
       -[Michelle] Yeah.        

05:37.671 --> 05:39.071
         -Oh, honey--           
     -Yeah, I have to go.       

05:39.073 --> 05:40.839
         I'm saying good morning
         and goodbye.           

05:40.841 --> 05:42.441
                  Love you guys.
                  Bye.          

05:42.443 --> 05:43.775
     -You need to eat more.     
     -Love you too.             

05:43.777 --> 05:45.010
          [Michelle]            
           I'll eat.            

05:45.012 --> 05:46.912
Just make sure                  
you get something.              

05:46.914 --> 05:48.580
      What's your plan?         
      Are you gonna go to Mohawk

05:48.582 --> 05:49.981
         and join your sister   

05:49.983 --> 05:51.817
        or are you gonna go     
        to one of the others?   

05:51.819 --> 05:53.051
        What are you thinking?  

05:53.053 --> 05:55.087
[Lenore]                        
These are your favorite.        

05:55.089 --> 05:58.557
  Actually, I wasn't planning   
on going to any camps this year.

05:58.559 --> 06:00.826
                   Excuse me?   

06:01.829 --> 06:03.695
Didn't I mention it?            
I thought I did.                

06:03.697 --> 06:05.664
           Uh, no, you didn't   
           mention it.          

06:05.666 --> 06:08.600
           You didn't mention it
           because...           

06:08.602 --> 06:10.402
             it's actually      
             not up to you      

06:10.404 --> 06:13.472
         to make                
         those decisions, chief.

06:13.474 --> 06:15.006
         I mean,                
         you can't hang out here

06:15.008 --> 06:17.142
         all summer             
         bothering your mother. 

06:17.144 --> 06:19.678
 She's got more important things
 to do than look after you.     

06:19.680 --> 06:22.414
 -[Lenore scoffs] Marty--       
 -You're going to camp, mister. 

06:22.416 --> 06:25.751
             And if you don't   
             choose one, I will.

06:25.753 --> 06:27.119
                         Okay?  

06:27.121 --> 06:29.020
           I'm going to go eat  
           on the porch.        

06:29.022 --> 06:31.523
       Let's have a good summer.

06:31.525 --> 06:33.158
    -[Marty] Eat some fruit.    
    -[Lenore] Huge test.        

06:33.160 --> 06:35.761
      [Marty] Fresh air!        
     It's why we're here.       

06:35.763 --> 06:37.729
  Hey, we'll talk               
  about it later, okay.         

06:37.731 --> 06:39.097
               Okay.            

06:39.099 --> 06:41.867
Let's just enjoy                
our breakfast, you and me.      

06:41.869 --> 06:44.035
      Like a date.              

06:44.037 --> 06:45.771
     -Kind of. It's weird.      
           -Uh, no.             

06:45.773 --> 06:46.805
         -Okay, sorry.          
     -That's weird, yeah.       

06:46.807 --> 06:48.440
      Definitely.               

06:48.442 --> 06:50.041
     -[people chattering]       
    -[game wheel clicking]      

06:50.043 --> 06:52.611
     [amusement park music      
    playing over speakers]      

06:54.615 --> 06:59.151
      [children screaming       
   in joyfully in distance]     

07:02.656 --> 07:04.089
        Been here long,         
       Joanie Williams?         

07:04.091 --> 07:06.958
Heh. Since they opened,         
Bobby Marks.                    

07:06.960 --> 07:09.828
  Oh. Here. Help me             
  finish my lemonade.           

07:09.830 --> 07:12.063
           [Robert]             
 <i> Let me make one thing clear:</i>  

07:12.065 --> 07:14.666
       <i> Joanie Williams</i>         
    <i> was not my girlfriend.</i>     

07:14.668 --> 07:16.034
                [clears throat] 

07:17.905 --> 07:19.838
                      What?     

07:19.840 --> 07:21.673
     Nothing.                   

07:21.675 --> 07:23.208
                  Yeah. Right.  

07:23.210 --> 07:25.744
         Well, I know you better
         than you know yourself 

07:25.746 --> 07:27.446
            and something's up  
            with you.           

07:27.448 --> 07:28.880
        <i> But we talked</i>          
  <i> about everything together.</i>   

07:28.882 --> 07:30.649
Come on.                        
Let's go have some fun.         

07:30.651 --> 07:32.684
    <i> I think the only thing</i>     
     <i> we didn't talk about</i>      

07:32.686 --> 07:36.855
   <i> was the size of her nose</i>    
  <i> and the size of my waist.</i>    

07:36.857 --> 07:38.557
 [Bobby] So, what do you want   
         to do first?           

07:38.559 --> 07:41.993
           [Joanie]             
Um, why don't we try that one?  

07:43.163 --> 07:45.964
 [Bobby] Really? Mr. Conceited  
        is running it.          

07:45.966 --> 07:49.000
           Bobby Marks,         
           are you jealous? Heh.

07:49.002 --> 07:50.836
            We got              
  some last-minute gamblers?    

07:50.838 --> 07:52.704
        -[Joanie] Yeah.         
         -Step on up.           

07:52.706 --> 07:54.940
    There's plenty of room      
   at the wheel of fortune.     

07:54.942 --> 07:56.975
       -[Joanie laughs]         
    -Feeling lucky tonight?     

07:56.977 --> 07:58.243
           [Joanie]             
          Yeah. Yeah.           

07:58.245 --> 08:01.146
 Go ahead and make your bets.   

08:01.148 --> 08:03.081
           [Robert]             
 <i> Everyone loved Pete Marino.</i>   

08:03.083 --> 08:05.617
   <i> Especially Pete Marino.</i>     

08:05.619 --> 08:07.118
That's a very good bet.         

08:07.120 --> 08:09.254
    [Pete and Joanie laugh]     

08:09.256 --> 08:10.856
             Okay.              

08:10.858 --> 08:13.592
        Round and round         
        the wheel goes.         

08:13.594 --> 08:17.629
-Where it stops, nobody knows.  
       -[girls laughing]        

08:23.036 --> 08:24.636
      -[Pete] Fourteen...       
-[Joanie laughing] Oh, my God!  

08:24.638 --> 08:27.005
      -We have a winner!        
      -Oh, my God. Okay.        

08:27.007 --> 08:28.573
You're the first                
big winner of the night.        

08:28.575 --> 08:29.608
        -Really? Okay.          
            -Yeah.              

08:29.610 --> 08:30.876
Uh, take your pick.             

08:30.878 --> 08:34.246
           Heh. Um...that one.  

08:37.885 --> 08:39.683
That one it is.                 

08:41.855 --> 08:43.154
Here you go, lucky lady.        

08:43.155 --> 08:45.090
                Thank you.      
                It's beautiful. 

08:45.092 --> 08:47.292
     Are we going to have       
 to lug that around all night?  

08:47.294 --> 08:49.861
Well, I don't mind              
watching him back here,         

08:49.863 --> 08:52.130
but, um, it might be            
better for business             

08:52.132 --> 08:53.798
if you carried him around       
for a bit.                      

08:53.800 --> 08:55.233
               Yeah. We're happy
               to help you      

08:55.235 --> 08:56.868
               in any way       
               we can, so...    

08:56.870 --> 08:58.270
Wonderful.                      

08:58.272 --> 09:00.605
                    [giggles]   

09:01.608 --> 09:03.775
         Isn't he just adorable?
         Heh.                   

09:03.777 --> 09:05.544
    Did he have something caught
    in his eye or something?    

09:05.546 --> 09:07.646
             Maybe we should    
             send over a doctor.

09:07.648 --> 09:10.181
    Also, wasn't there some     
sort of dress code or something?

09:10.183 --> 09:13.318
              I mean, if not,   
              there should be.  

09:13.320 --> 09:16.555
Do you think he owns any clothes
    that actually fit him?      

09:16.557 --> 09:19.291
  -[metallic clang from game]   
-[Bobby] Hey, let's go this way.

09:21.028 --> 09:23.028
                 Bobby Marks?   

09:23.931 --> 09:25.730
  Joanie Williams?              

09:25.732 --> 09:28.733
           We're going back     
           to the city tomorrow.

09:30.337 --> 09:33.038
      What?                     

09:33.040 --> 09:34.806
We just got here.               
Why?                            

09:34.808 --> 09:36.041
               I, I don't know. 

09:36.043 --> 09:38.076
        -For how long?          
         -A few weeks.          

09:38.078 --> 09:39.678
                Maybe a month.  

09:39.680 --> 09:40.979
            -Maybe.             
           -A month?            

09:40.981 --> 09:42.814
              Maybe.            
              We don't know yet.

09:44.918 --> 09:47.252
     Um...                      

09:47.254 --> 09:48.853
Look, wait.                     
You don't have to go.           

09:48.855 --> 09:50.322
You can stay with us.           

09:50.324 --> 09:52.824
You can have my room            
and I'll sleep on the couch.    

09:52.826 --> 09:54.225
           No, I have to go too.

09:54.227 --> 09:56.227
             -Why?              
        -Just because.          

09:56.229 --> 09:57.963
That's not an answer.           
Just tell me why.               

09:57.965 --> 10:00.732
              Don't be so pushy.
              Jeez.             

10:06.239 --> 10:09.274
[mechanical game motor whirring]

10:14.147 --> 10:15.714
          You're going          
          to miss the fireworks.

10:15.716 --> 10:17.215
           They're gonna be huge
           this year.           

10:17.217 --> 10:18.850
     Are you trying             
     to make it worse?          

10:18.852 --> 10:21.119
              No.               

10:21.121 --> 10:24.990
        Sorry, it's...          
       Well, you know...        

10:24.992 --> 10:26.658
              I know.           
              But you know what,

10:26.660 --> 10:28.793
              you're gonna find 
              something to do.  

10:28.795 --> 10:30.395
         And it's gonna be fine.

10:30.397 --> 10:33.732
          -Like what?           
-Like, why don't you get a job? 

10:33.734 --> 10:35.300
 -[Bobby laughs incredulously]  
            -What?              

10:35.302 --> 10:37.869
There's always postings         
on the bulletin board.          

10:37.871 --> 10:39.671
            Yeah.               
            For baby-sitting.   

10:39.673 --> 10:40.939
 Or gardening.                  

10:40.941 --> 10:42.140
You could do                    
something like that.            

10:42.142 --> 10:43.875
      -[Bobby] Uh, okay.        
            -C'mon.             

10:43.877 --> 10:45.176
                 I don't know.  

10:45.178 --> 10:46.711
             I mean, it's       
             pretty hard work.  

10:46.713 --> 10:48.413
             And besides,       
             who would hire me  

10:48.415 --> 10:50.882
         when there's, you know,
         older kids around?     

10:50.884 --> 10:53.251
    You look older.             
    Hold this.                  

10:54.388 --> 10:56.187
           Hmm...               

10:56.189 --> 10:58.256
You're not gonna                
find anything.                  

10:58.258 --> 11:02.027
    "Boy needed for maintaining 
    large estate on Rumson Lake.

11:02.029 --> 11:03.962
         Two dollars per hour." 

11:03.964 --> 11:05.397
      You could totally do that.

11:05.399 --> 11:07.032
   I. No.                       

11:07.034 --> 11:09.834
               Heh. Yeah.       
               We're gonna call.

11:09.836 --> 11:11.369
                 Come on.       

11:11.371 --> 11:16.374
Uh, hold on, wait, no.          
No, we're not calling.          

11:16.376 --> 11:18.910
            -Call.              
  -No, I don't want to call.    

11:18.912 --> 11:20.245
                         Why?   

11:20.247 --> 11:21.913
'Cause I don't want             
to do the job, okay?            

11:21.915 --> 11:23.782
           [Willie]             
      Watch your fingers.       

11:23.784 --> 11:26.084
-He probably thinks it's food.  
          -[laughter]           

11:26.086 --> 11:27.786
           [Robert]             
    <i> There was a time when</i>      

11:27.788 --> 11:30.121
    <i> Willie Rumson's family</i>     
    <i> owned the whole lake.</i>      

11:32.159 --> 11:34.159
      <i> for nearly killing</i>       
     <i> some guy in a fight.</i>      

11:34.161 --> 11:36.027
     [laughter continues]       

11:36.029 --> 11:37.962
[Willie] That's a very nice bear
  you got there, little girl.   

11:37.964 --> 11:39.431
          -Let's go.            
            -Call.              

11:39.433 --> 11:40.765
    No. Come on.                

11:41.368 --> 11:42.901
The wicked witch gave you       

11:42.903 --> 11:44.769
an order, little dough boy.     

11:44.771 --> 11:48.940
You'd better obey or she'll get 
you-- and your little dog too.  

11:48.942 --> 11:51.276
[mockingly laughs]              

11:52.212 --> 11:54.479
 [chuckles]                     

11:54.481 --> 11:56.481
Don't you point                 
that nose at me.                

11:56.483 --> 11:58.149
Thing might be                  
fricking loaded!                

11:58.151 --> 12:00.351
       [young men laugh]        

12:00.353 --> 12:02.253
            [Pete]              
          Hey, Rummy.           

12:04.124 --> 12:06.891
  Time to get going.            

12:06.893 --> 12:08.493
It's                            
a free country, Wop.            

12:08.495 --> 12:11.329
Yeah, well, the club            
is members only.                

12:11.331 --> 12:14.466
No townie trash, so, uh...      

12:14.468 --> 12:15.900
      [chuckles]                

12:15.902 --> 12:17.502
 That's not nice. Heh.          

12:17.504 --> 12:19.504
    [Jim] This place sucks      
        anyway, Willie.         

12:31.485 --> 12:33.284
Your shirt's                    
really small, man.              

12:33.286 --> 12:35.787
      [young men chuckle]       

12:35.789 --> 12:37.255
    Put the cigarettes out.     

12:37.257 --> 12:39.324
I'm pretty sure they sell       
men's sizes in town...          

12:39.326 --> 12:41.426
[young men laugh]               

12:41.428 --> 12:45.396
Listen, man, don't worry about  
those losers, all right?        

12:49.035 --> 12:51.803
             [¶¶]               

12:54.274 --> 12:56.241
         Promise me you'll call.

12:59.012 --> 13:02.814
Okay. Fine. I'll call.          

13:02.816 --> 13:04.249
                     Thank you. 

13:04.251 --> 13:06.885
           I wish you lots      
           of luck, Bobby Marks.

13:06.887 --> 13:08.820
           And I'll be back     
           in a few weeks, so...

13:08.822 --> 13:10.255
                   I promise.   

13:10.257 --> 13:12.490
                  Muah. Heh.    

13:12.492 --> 13:14.025
                    Bye.        

13:14.027 --> 13:15.527
        Bye.                    

13:20.934 --> 13:23.268
             [¶¶]               

14:14.621 --> 14:18.089
You are the boy                 
who telephoned about the job?   

14:18.091 --> 14:21.092
            [Bobby]             
         Uh, yes, sir.          

14:21.094 --> 14:22.861
Robert Marks.                   

14:22.863 --> 14:24.529
            You walked here.    

14:25.432 --> 14:27.398
        I like                  
        a boy with enterprise.  

14:28.201 --> 14:30.001
              How old are you?  

14:30.003 --> 14:31.236
        Uh...                   

14:31.238 --> 14:32.971
                Speak up, boy.  

14:34.107 --> 14:36.608
          -Seventeen.           
          -Seventeen?           

14:39.512 --> 14:42.046
       Have you done            
       this sort of work before?

14:42.048 --> 14:44.249
Uh...no, sir.                   

14:44.251 --> 14:46.217
Not yet.                        

14:46.219 --> 14:49.454
       Well then, I don't think 
       you're right for the job.

14:49.456 --> 14:52.957
     It's not easy work and this
     is not a small property.   

14:54.127 --> 14:57.629
  Oh. Uh, okay...               

14:59.199 --> 15:01.499
                 That is it?    

15:02.269 --> 15:04.002
 Sir?                           

15:04.004 --> 15:06.971
       You're not going to fight
       for it, for the job?     

15:06.973 --> 15:10.275
Uh...I don't understand.        

15:10.277 --> 15:12.443
          You want the job, yes?

15:12.445 --> 15:14.646
              Then you should   
              not acquiesce     

15:14.648 --> 15:17.348
              and accept my no  
              as the final no.  

15:17.350 --> 15:20.051
       You should try           
       to convince me otherwise.

15:20.053 --> 15:21.352
Convince you?                   

15:21.354 --> 15:22.921
                       Indeed.  

15:22.923 --> 15:26.624
Uh. Well, I'm sure              
I can do this job, sir,         

15:26.626 --> 15:28.192
if you just give me             
a chance--                      

15:28.194 --> 15:29.294
      I don't have time to train

15:29.296 --> 15:31.329
           a boy with no skills.

15:31.331 --> 15:33.131
    Oh. Um...                   

15:34.301 --> 15:36.501
Well, uh,                       
I learn really quick.           

15:36.503 --> 15:38.569
           -Quickly.            
   -And all my teachers say     

15:38.571 --> 15:40.305
I'm bright                      
and a good worker.              

