    <i> are being broken here.</i>     

35:36.602 --> 35:39.302
         ...at the new rate     
         of one dollar per hour.

35:39.304 --> 35:42.339
      [Robert] <i> But it was</i>       
<i>the first money I'd ever made.</i>  

36:04.530 --> 36:06.696
            Ah, did you quit    
            my job yet?         

36:06.698 --> 36:08.431
               Look at me.      

36:11.670 --> 36:15.672
You and your kind come up here  
for two months a year           

36:15.674 --> 36:20.243
and you act like it's yours,    
but it ain't.                   

36:23.549 --> 36:25.382
              It's got your name
              on it, Willie.    

36:25.384 --> 36:28.251
     That's right, Dougie.      

36:28.253 --> 36:31.755
      My great-grandpa--        
      he owned all this.        

36:31.757 --> 36:35.625
      So, I get to decide       
   what's what around here.     

36:35.627 --> 36:37.561
      What you got there?       

36:37.563 --> 36:39.196
 Nothing.                       

36:39.198 --> 36:42.265
      Heh. Well, it doesn't     
      look like nothing.        

36:43.335 --> 36:46.269
Come on, hey. No...             

36:51.610 --> 36:53.610
   That's it?                   

36:53.612 --> 36:56.213
   [laughs]                     

36:56.215 --> 36:58.648
That old kike                   
is ripping you off, boy.        

36:58.650 --> 37:02.219
Hey. Didn't I say               
it was my job?                  

37:02.221 --> 37:05.622
Well, that would make it        
my money. Right?                

37:05.624 --> 37:06.990
       [car approaching]        

37:06.992 --> 37:09.392
Well, do you have               
a problem with that?            

37:10.562 --> 37:12.462
     [police siren chirps]      

37:17.769 --> 37:19.469
          Hold up, hold up.     

37:19.471 --> 37:20.804
     Uncle Hank.                

37:20.806 --> 37:23.306
            What you got here,  
            Willie?             

37:23.308 --> 37:25.875
This delinquent was trying      
to throw a rock                 

37:25.877 --> 37:27.944
    -through my windshield.     
      -No! No, I wasn't!        

37:27.946 --> 37:29.546
            [Hank]              
Didn't your folks ever tell you 

37:29.548 --> 37:31.615
     not to throw stones?       

37:31.617 --> 37:33.350
          What's your name?     

37:33.352 --> 37:37.287
[sighs]                         
Robert Marks.                   

37:37.289 --> 37:38.488
        Summer people?          

37:41.994 --> 37:45.495
  Seems like all my problems    
 are caused by summer people.   

37:47.399 --> 37:49.366
           [Willie]             
   Well, that's exactly what    
   I was saying to the guys.    

37:49.368 --> 37:51.901
     Yeah. Coming up here       
 with your big city attitudes   

37:51.903 --> 37:53.837
 and bothering all the locals   

37:53.839 --> 37:56.640
      who don't cause me        
    any problems all year.      

37:56.642 --> 37:58.008
           -No, I--             
     -[Hank] That's right.      

37:58.010 --> 37:59.909
    It's all about I, I, I,     
          me, me, me            

37:59.911 --> 38:01.711
  with you people, isn't it?    
      Well, the next time       

38:01.713 --> 38:03.313
          I catch you           
     harassing the locals,      

38:03.315 --> 38:04.914
           I'm going            
  to have to call your folks    

38:04.916 --> 38:06.316
       so they can come         
     bail you out of jail.      

38:06.318 --> 38:08.285
        You understand?         

38:08.287 --> 38:10.387
         All I hear is          
  your brains rattling around   

38:10.389 --> 38:11.721
  in that fat head of yours.    

38:11.723 --> 38:12.789
          I asked you           
      if you understand.        

38:12.791 --> 38:14.758
          -Yes, sir.            
            -Good.              

38:16.328 --> 38:17.794
        [under breath]          
     Now get out of here.       

38:17.796 --> 38:19.496
        [men chuckling]         

38:28.807 --> 38:31.808
             [¶¶]               

39:39.144 --> 39:40.744
       Hey, sleepyhead.         

39:40.746 --> 39:43.146
[Bobby groans]                  

39:44.449 --> 39:46.149
             You slept through  
             another dinner.    

39:46.151 --> 39:48.852
          I'm starting to really
          worry about you.      

39:48.854 --> 39:51.521
I got up and ate                
something last night.           

39:51.523 --> 39:53.823
Besides, you don't have         
to worry about me.              

39:53.825 --> 39:55.158
I'm not a kid anymore.          

39:55.160 --> 39:56.893
          I'm always            
          gonna worry about you.

39:56.895 --> 39:59.028
          It doesn't matter     
          how old you are.      

39:59.030 --> 40:01.464
          When I close my eyes  
          and I think about you,

40:01.466 --> 40:03.900
               I still see you  
